{
  "texts": [
    "While the first criterion is straightforward to evaluate, the latter is not directly available, since the current number of leaf cells differs from the number of cells in the original mesh.",
    "Suppose that M ∈ R N ℓ is a vector holding the approximated metric of all N ℓ leaf cells.",
    "To stop the refinement, we measure the captured metric as the ratio of the vector norms and compare it to a user-defined threshold value, i.e., stop if Mapprox = || M||/||M|| ≥ Mmin.",
    "Note that approximation errors in M may cancel out when comparing the norms.",
    "However, we found the impact of this cancellation to be negligible."
  ]
}